      • withEqualityPairs

        public final CollectionCmpBuilder<B,W> withEqualityPairs(java.util.List<EqualityPair<B,W>> equalityPairs)
        Compare matched items based on equality pairs. All equality pairs must match in order for items to be considered equal.

        Equality is a function that takes item as an input parameter and returns a value. Two items are considered equal if the results of all it's equality pairs are equal.

        You can use this option to compare items of same type based on a few of their fields.

        Parameters:
        equalityPairs - equality pairs based on which objects are compared
        Returns:
        builder instance
        See Also:
        EqualityPair
